  "original_title": "\u0daf\u0dd4\u0db8\u0dca\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0dba \u0d9c\u0dcf\u0dc3\u0dca\u0dad\u0dd4 \u0dc0\u0dd0\u0da9\u0dd2 \u0db1\u0ddc\u0d9a\u0dbb\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1\u0dd0\u0dba\u0dd2 \u0d89\u0dbd\u0dca\u0dbd\u0dd3\u0db8\u0d9a\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "A request not to increase railway fares",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "At a time when thousands of people in the country are facing problems, the Coastal Railway Passengers Union requests not to increase the train fares.",
        "The president of the association, Mr. Gunapala Janadhi Witharana, made this request at a press conference held at the Galle Southern Lanka Media Center this evening (21). He also said:",
        "\"Railway fares are going to increase. Don't do this. Delay this rate hike for some more time. Now the people are in trouble. There was only this train to travel. In recent days, we have seen people hanging from the train and climbing on the roof. If the train is lost, the people will have nothing to do. There are fewer buses today. Buses are packed with people. The train was a relief to the people as there was no fuel.",
        "The way it is going, that relief will disappear. Bus fares increased. Used to travel by train. Railways is a service department, not a money making department. Therefore, we request to change the decision taken and give relief to the people who fell into the frying pan."
      ],
